<TEXT>
immigration agents reportedly acting 
on a tip that terrorists with iraqi connections had entered the 
united states raided a churchoperated shelter for central american 
immigrants thursday 
immigration officials previously had maintained a handsoff 
policy toward casa romero operated by the roman catholic diocese 
of brownsville because it is considered a church thirtyfive 
people were arrested 
silvestre reyes chief patrol agent with the us border 
patrols mcallen sector said immigration officials obtained the 
search warrant after learning that there might be 21 indians 
pakistanis and iranians there he said officials particularly were 
interested in finding individuals from the sikh religious sect of 
india 
we have some information regarding national security regarding 
those individuals reyes said 
five indians two pakistanis four guyanese two salvadorans 
six hondurans a guatemalan and 15 who said they were mexican were 
arrested at casa romero for allegedly being in the country 
illegally reyes said 
reyes said officials believe some of those identifying 
themselves as mexicans might be actually be from india 
an immigration official who asked not to be identified said the 
agents had obtained intelligence reports that terrorists were 
trying to enter the united states to carry out actions on behalf of 
iraq iraqi leader saddam hussein has threatened terrorist strikes 
since the us military buildup began in the persian gulf in 
response to iraqs aug 2 invasion of kuwait 
about 25 us border patrol agents with a search warrant entered 
the sixacre compound while residents were in line for dinner 
theyre scared sister norma pimentel shelter director 
said of the immigrants after the raid they dont know why this 
happened 
the shelter opened in 1982 in san benito and moved to the 
outskirts of brownsville in 1987 the area around brownsville 
texas southernmost city on the mexican border is a popular 
crossing point for central americans because it is the closest 
us point by land to that region 
reyes said although it was the first time the border patrol had 
entered the shelter with a search warrant he always had maintained 
the right to enter 
he said six indians arrested at kingsville in south texas 
earlier thursday told agents that alien smugglers had made 
arrangements for their trip at casa romero and had picked them up 
there 
the shelter is named for monsignor oscar romero who was gunned 
down while saying mass in el salvadora on march 24 1980 
</TEXT>
