prabhat aggarwal knows by his very name 
his place in life aggarwal is also his caste 
aggarwals were the masters of the economy in india kings and 
rajas were dependent on us we were the moneylenders the 
17yearold student said 
aggarwal whose caste puts him in the upper rank of indian 
society was on a downtown street demonstrating against prime 
minister vp singhs policy to reserve more government jobs for 
lowcaste indians 
singh described the policy as a glimmer of hope to those who 
have known only oppression for centuries because of their caste 
he said wednesday he would rather quit than barter away the 
aspirations of the deprived 
uppercaste students angered and feeling threatened that jobs 
historically dominated by their classes would be reserved for the 
lower castes have rioted across northern india crippling new 
delhi for several days this week 
on sept 19 a 20yearold uppercaste student rajeev goswami 
doused himself with gasoline and lit a match goswami survived but 
seven other students and a farmer have committed suicide and 
dozens have tried fortysix have died in clashes with police 
which prompted officials thursday to declare curfews in eight 
cities 
we love mother india aggarwal complained but when a 
mother says one child is good and the other is bad what can we 
