<TEXT>
by 1944 army careerist dwight david 
eisenhower had five stars an allied forces command but no 
hometown 
for years the man who later became the nations 34th president 
had incorrectly given tyler texas as his birthplace 
enter jennie jackson a retired schoolteacher principal and 
amateur historian in denison a small town 70 miles north of 
dallas 
she remembered rocking an eisenhower infant on her knee in 1890 
and wondered if it was the general 
she secretly wrote eisenhower who told her to contact his 
mother ida she wrote back confirming the general was indeed the 
same david eisenhower miss jackson remembered 
she then went public with a campaign to save the small clapboard 
house where eisenhower was born 
miss jackson died shortly after she persuaded the city to buy 
