the acquittals and ordered a new trial saying marcos engineered 
the original verdict 
the first trial was marked by frequent street demonstrations and 
rallies but the second attracted virtually no spectators apart 
from relatives of the accused newspapers rarely covered it 
the aquino case has often been cited as an example of the 
countrys inefficient judiciary midway during the proceedings the 
supreme court disbarred chief prosecutor raul gonzalez after he 
publicly charged justices were misappropriating funds 
one defendant died during the trial and three others including 
ver have fled the country philippine law does not permit trials 
in absentia 
