obrien was elected to succeed the late walter kennedy as nba 
commissioner in 1975 a year when free agency and big money were 
reshaping pro sports 
it was with obriens guidance that the nba settled the 
socalled oscar robertson suit in 1976 which paved the way to 
free agency in the league the nba and its players association also 
reached a collective bargaining agreement 
he also supervised the nbas merger with the rival american 
basketball association as a result the four strongest teams from 
the aba were absorbed into the nba the move ended costly feuding 
between the two leagues 
in 1983 obrien and the nba seemed headed toward a crisis as 
the playoffs approached so the did the possibility of a players 
strike obrien helped negotiate a new collective bargaining 
agreement between the nba and the players association 
the agreement provided for a cap on how much money teams could 
spend on salaries and benefits in return for which the players 
were guaranteed 53 percent of the gross revenues of the league the 
pact hailed by owners and players as a major step toward securing 
the leagues stability was a landmark labor agreement in 
professional sports 
its a tribute to him that a strike was avoided said julius 
erving one of the leagues best and most respected players 
in november 1983 obrien announced that he had declined a new 
fiveyear contract there comes a time when you have to move 
on he said he left the post the following year 
i think the sport is better off by far than it was in 1975 
