step backward from the legislation already approved by the house 
and senate rep henry waxman dcalif in turn accused the 
senators of misunderstanding the offer 
i dont think youve looked at this proposal he told 
senators 
at the heart of the sometimes raucous debate was concern also 
expressed by state pollution control officials that the house 
proposal would prevent other states from adopting the strong auto 
pollution control measures being taken by california 
there was also concern that an ambitious program to require the 
use of alternativefuel vehicles by fleet operators and a separate 
pilot program for alternativefuel personal passenger cars were 
being weakened 
