<TEXT>
martin shugrue was telling a campus audience the 
other day that his 100 days campaign at eastern was a victory 
what victory shouted one of the striking eastern machinists 
union members who joined students for shugrues speech at florida 
international university 
survival dear friend survival was shugrues answer 
but even that minimal accomplishment is in doubt as an airline 
industry downturn steepened by soaring oil prices worsens 
easterns viability 
its worse because everybodys worse said robert joedicke 
airline analyst for shearson lehman brothers inc theres no way 
you can make up the immediate rise in fuel prices 
jet fuel prices have soared since iraq invaded kuwait on aug 2 
driving up the cost of oil the major airlines have increased fares 
some of them twice but with passenger traffic already sluggish 
they cant raise them to match the higher fuel costs 
for eastern things are even worse like most carriers 
theyre between the rock and the hard place joedicke said not 
only that the airline was already in a financial bind thats a 
hard thing to carry on 
eastern filed for chapter 11 bankruptcy protection 1 years ago 
and has seen operating losses continue at more than 2 million a 
day its secondquarter operating loss was 2344 million and 
shugrue has indicated thirdquarter results wont be comforting for 
increasingly nervous creditors 
