persian gulf crisis which has increased easterns fuel costs from 
56 cents a gallon to 96 cents it came he said as the airline was 
making progress 
in august its load capacity was 72 percent eastern was showing 
its strongest signs of progress since it began rebuilding from the 
crippling march 4 1989 strike led by machinists and joined by 
pilots and flight attendants after years of labormanagement 
tension 
the company also recently announced a major push to draw 
